The paper deals with dynamic algorithms for graph sparsification problems, which are primarily studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The use of spectral sparsifiers and cut sparsifiers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the application of the dynamic sparsifier algorithm to maximum flow in bipartite graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
